17:23.025 --> 17:25.043
♪ ♪

17:46.566 --> 17:49.734
Have you ever heard
Lisa make that sound?

17:49.885 --> 17:51.402
I've heard her laugh before,

17:51.629 --> 17:53.796
but it's always been ironic.
Or sarcastic.

17:53.815 --> 17:57.108
Or dubiously polite and
just a little bit put-upon.

17:57.260 --> 17:59.726
(laughing continuing)

17:59.746 --> 18:01.728
But never that.

18:01.806 --> 18:02.938
-Aw.
-Aw.

18:02.990 --> 18:06.325
Once again, cartoon violence
and mental health

18:06.477 --> 18:08.377
go hand in hand.

18:09.480 --> 18:11.814
So, how late
did you two crazy kids

18:11.907 --> 18:13.407
stay up watching cartoons?

18:13.501 --> 18:15.985
I don't know,
but all the ads on TV

18:16.078 --> 18:17.320
were about calling women

18:17.322 --> 18:20.581
who couldn't wait
to talk to us right now.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.433
I'm glad you had fun.

18:23.603 --> 18:24.827
Well, that's odd.

18:24.920 --> 18:26.829
Maggie never
liked that book before.

18:26.922 --> 18:28.314
I zazzed it up for her.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.504
Oh, you wrote Maggie
into the story.

18:35.598 --> 18:38.357
What a special
little guy you are.

18:38.509 --> 18:41.410
Eh, no way.
I just wanted to deface a book.

18:42.697 --> 18:44.330
Sure you did.

18:46.534 --> 18:47.625
Morning, folks.

18:47.776 --> 18:49.610
Why'd you break down our door?

18:49.629 --> 18:51.537
Oh, we do that for everyone now.

18:51.631 --> 18:52.779
So, good news.

18:52.799 --> 18:55.541
I'm taking Bart away forever.
(chuckles)

18:55.693 --> 18:58.377
Oh. So you figured
out where he's from?

18:58.529 --> 19:00.696
No, but I went
to the courthouse,

19:00.715 --> 19:02.198
and one of those, uh, uh,

19:02.200 --> 19:04.566
robe-and-gavel guys
said to dump him

19:04.702 --> 19:07.311
at the Springfield
Maximum Security Orphanage.

19:07.463 --> 19:09.872
Uh, it used to be a prison,
but don't worry.

19:09.965 --> 19:12.541
None of the old guards
lost their jobs.

19:12.635 --> 19:15.544
You know, we could hang on
to Bart for a little while,

19:15.563 --> 19:17.804
if you want to
keep working on his case.

19:17.824 --> 19:19.031
No, thank you.

19:20.067 --> 19:22.827
Oh, hey, don't worry about it.

19:22.978 --> 19:24.645
I knew this was
a short-term gig,

19:24.664 --> 19:27.498
and I'll always have
something to remember you by.

19:28.651 --> 19:30.585
Why you little....

19:31.654 --> 19:34.321
Adios, losers.

19:34.340 --> 19:36.081
Next time you see
a mouse kill a cat

19:36.234 --> 19:38.509
in a way you never thought
possible, think of me.

19:38.661 --> 19:40.219
I will.

19:46.594 --> 19:49.220
Bart! Come back!

19:49.355 --> 19:52.172
We like you.
God help us, we like you.

19:52.266 --> 19:54.692
We like you so much.

19:55.695 --> 19:57.102
Stop!

19:57.255 --> 19:58.696
Don't take him!

20:11.936 --> 20:12.859
You're still here.

20:13.028 --> 20:14.770
My beautiful, wonderful boy

20:14.789 --> 20:16.714
is still here.

20:17.884 --> 20:19.199
(grunts)
Ow.

20:19.277 --> 20:20.793
What the hell?
Get off.

20:20.887 --> 20:22.278
I'm sorry, son.

20:22.296 --> 20:25.556
We just couldn't wait
to tell you something.

20:25.783 --> 20:27.541
We like you.

20:27.560 --> 20:29.785
We like our son so much.

20:29.804 --> 20:31.712
We just realized.

20:31.731 --> 20:33.064
Mm, I like you guys, too.

